{% if "RAG_OVER_PII" in active_risks %}

## Detected risks — mandatory measures

### Critical: RAG over personal data (GDPR Art. 25)

**Risk:** A vector database + LLM API were detected in the stack.
On RAG queries, embeddings containing personal content are inserted
directly into the LLM prompt — the LLM processes PII without the
user's knowledge.

**Typical cases:**
- Vector database with a personal-data table as the embedding source
- RAG over support tickets, contracts or customer data
- Semantic search without prior PII filtering

**Mandatory measures:** UUID-only pattern (embed anonymised chunks only),
PII scrubbing before embedding generation (e.g. Presidio), no user.email / user.name
in embedding documents, document access control on the vector store.

**Legal basis:** GDPR Art. 25 (Privacy by Design),
Art. 32 (technical protective measures),
Art. 5 (data minimisation), EU AI Act Art. 10

{% elif "PII_IN_LLM_CONTEXT" in active_risks %}

## Detected risks — mandatory measures

### PII risk: database data in the LLM context (GDPR Art. 25)

**Risk:** LLM API and database access in the same stack.
Personal data could reach the LLM context unfiltered.

**Recommended measures:** UUID-only pattern (Neo4j/LLM with anonymised IDs only),
PII stays local (post-retrieval join in the application layer),
alternatively Presidio as a PII pre-filter before the LLM call.

**Legal basis:** GDPR Art. 25, Art. 32, EU AI Act Art. 10

{% endif %}

{% if "PII_IN_LOGS" in active_risks %}

### PII in logs: monitoring + LLM detected (GDPR Art. 32)

**Risk:** Without explicit measures, PII ends up in error logs
of monitoring services (Sentry, Datadog) — often persistent
and outside the EU perimeter.

**Mandatory measures:** error logging with UUID prefix only (never real names/emails),
configure log scrubbing before external transmission, document retention policies for logs.

{% endif %}

